Korea-Bulgarian Summit to Expand Cooperation in Nuclear Power Plants and Defense Industries (Bulgarian) | Yahoo!
(SEOUL=Yonhap News) South Korean President Moon Jae-in met with Bulgaria's Prime Minister Borisov on his official visit to Korea on September 27 and discussed ways to expand bilateral cooperation.
This is the first time the Prime Minister of Bulgaria has visited Korea.
President Moon welcomed the visit to Korea before the 30th anniversary of the establishment of diplomatic relations next year and appreciated the leadership of Prime Minister Borisov, who leads the development of Bulgaria.
The two leaders appreciated the continued increase in trade and investment between the two countries amid the global expansion of protectionism and agreed to work together to expand economic cooperation in the future.
President Moon welcomed Bulgaria's policy of granting Korean companies the status of "strategic investors" and said that he hoped that this would help Korean companies to invest in Bulgaria.
He also stressed that South Korea will be the best partner for Bulgaria as Bulgaria is promoting the introduction of nuclear power plants and the modernization of defense, and called for attention and cooperation so that Korean companies can participate in the order of the Bulgarian government's nuclear power plants and the promotion of the defense industry.
In addition, the two leaders agreed to strengthen future-oriented cooperation in the areas of battery and auto parts for electric vehicles and renewable energy.
Prime Minister Borisov hoped that Korea's leading ICT (information and communication technology) will cooperate closely in the fields of science, technology and education.
They also discussed the peace process on the Korean Peninsula, and President Moon expressed his gratitude for the support of the Korean government's efforts to establish peace on the Korean Peninsula, including the announcement by Bulgaria in support of the North-South and North-America Summits.
Prime Minister Borisov appreciated President Moon's will to build a peace regime on the Korean peninsula and the efforts of the Korean government, and reiterated the firm support of the Bulgarian government.
The meeting was attended by the Secretary of the Ministry of Trade, Industry and Energy, Sung Yunmo, Lee Hao-sho, Chief Economic Secretary of the Chong Chong (President's Office) and Kim Hyun-jong, Second Director of the National Security Office.
During his visit to the U.S., Mr. Kang Gyeong-fa, deputy director of the Ministry of Foreign Affairs, also attended the meeting.
Local industry in Hyogo and Awaji Island, Kinki Ceramics Co., Ltd., a manufacturer of Awaji tiles, filed for quasi-self-insolvency Liabilities of approximately 2 billion yen (Imperial Data Bank) - Yahoo!
It was also affected by the sluggish housing market and the progress of "consumer roofing away" due to the frequent disaster.
Kinki Ceramics Co., Ltd. (TDB Corporation Code:53173983, capital of 9.92 million yen, 881-8 Otani, Awaji City, Hyogo Prefecture, representative Yukizo Fukuhara and 44 employees) filed for quasi-self-insolvency at the Kobe District Court on August 30.
One applicant was Daichi Yoshida (1-10-8 Nishitenman, Kita Ward, Osaka City, Osaka Prefecture, and Daichi Yoshida Law Office, telephone number 06-6365-6038).
The company was founded in June 1895 and reorganized in April 1961.
At first, he started his business as a manufacturer of ibushi tiles, a local industry in Awaji Island, in Nishitan-cho, Mihara County (now Minamiawaji City) under the trade name of Kinki Kiln Co., Ltd.
In October 1986, Kyowa Kiln Co., Ltd. merged into Kyowa Kiln Co., Ltd., succeeded the business of Kinki Sangyo Co., Ltd., and at the same time, the head office was moved to the present location after changing the business name.
After that, sales offices were established in Fukuyama City, Hiroshima City, Oita City, Miyazaki City, etc., and it became the current system, and Ibushi-gawara was mainly used before, but due to changes in consumer needs, Western-style tiles such as flat-paned tiles were manufactured at 70%, and Ibushi-gawara was manufactured at 30%.
The company has established a wide range of sales bases mainly in western Japan, including major house manufacturers, construction materials trading companies, and roof construction companies.
He was well known as the top tile maker of Awaji Island.
However, demand continued to grow due to the sluggish housing market following the Lehman shock and the frequent disaster such as the Great East Japan Earthquake and the Kumamoto Earthquake.
In terms of profits, in addition to a decline in profitability due to the surge in fuel prices, the company suffered a continuous deficit due to excessive interest-bearing debt associated with inventory burdens and business fixed investment, and was forced to make a severe financial position.
For this reason, the Bank sought to rebuild its business by requesting financial institutions to ease the conditions for repayment of loans, but there were no signs of recovery in business conditions, and the funding situation gradually became tight.
He was unable to support the project and gave up on continuing the business.
The debt is currently under investigation, but it is estimated to be about 2 billion yen.
Prefectural Dinosaur Museum in Katsuyama City, Fukui Prefecture, which promotes the industrialization of tourism (photographed by Japanese aerial photographs and small drones)
Katsuyama City, Fukui Prefecture announced on September 25 that it will acquire approximately 25,000 square meters of land adjacent to the construction site of the road station "Dinosaur Valley Katsuyama," which will open next spring.
In order to accelerate the "industrialization of tourism" advocated by the city and the local economy, we aim to attract accommodation-specific hotels and restaurants.
On the same day, the Board of Directors of the Special Committee for the Improvement of Invited Facilities of the City Council explained.
In addition to the opening of the Hokuriku Shinkansen in the spring of 2023, the entire section of the Chubu Centrair Expressway will be opened, and the prefectural Dinosaur Museum (Katsuyama City) will be expanded and renovated.
It is a private idle land next to the east of the road station construction site.
Surrounded by the Kuzuryu River, Takinami River and the prefectural road, it is more than twice the size of a roadside station (about 12,000 square meters).
In the name of the industrial complex, the City Land Development Corporation will proceed with land negotiations from this fiscal year and build land in FY21 after acquiring land.
According to the city, private businesses such as farmers' restaurants and harvest experience facilities, fast food, and restaurants are already looking to enter the market.
As for accommodation, it was also revealed that Sekisui House has promoted its name as a city to attract accommodation-specific hotels adjacent to Michi No Eki, which is planned nationwide.
Sekisui House plans to expand into three locations within Fukui Prefecture, but it is said that there are other cities and towns that are willing to attract and may compete.
The city also plans to build a parking lot.
Some members called for speed-up when the maintenance schedule was slow, and others said that there was no place to sleep.
Vice Mayor Sanekio Mizukami expressed his determination to attract hotels and other facilities as a tourism-themed industrial complex.
