BITPoint, which leaked 3 billion yen worth of crypto assets, to resume service (Genfusha Gold Online) - Yahoo!
In July of this year, crypto asset exchanges, which amounted to 3 billion yen such as bitcoin, leaked illegally.
Bitpoint Japan Co., Ltd., which is the operator, announced on September 30 that it will resume the sending (remittance) service of crypto assets.
There seems to be a certain point of view, including measures to prevent recurrence.
BITPoint spilled Bitcoin and Ripple this July.
Bitpoint Japan Co., Ltd., which operates the Crypto Asset Exchange BITPoint, announced on September 27 that it will resume the service of sending (remittance) crypto assets at around 14:00 on September 30.
In addition to responding to customers and communicating with the Financial Services Agency, there seems to be a certain point of view, including measures to prevent recurrence, such as management management system including security.
Bitpoint Japan says, "We will resume the service as soon as possible, while putting safety first, and strive to recover the trust of users."
In July of this year, cryptocurrency assets such as Bitcoin and Ripple were leaked to the exchange.
In the subsequent press conference, regarding the continuation of the business, he mentioned that "there is a current account balance of about 3 billion yen even if the compensation is subtracted" "We aim to resume the service as soon as possible based on the priority of user protection."
This article was released on September 27, 2019.
