Self-improvement of safety measures at Famaspo 35 percent of municipalities implemented, free of charge for child care|Shizuoka Shimbun
Bereaved families (right) of the child-care accident to press a press conference on the results of the "Family Support Center Project" = On the afternoon of the 27th, Osaka Prefecture Agency
According to a private survey on the 27th, 35% of municipal towns and villages that implement the Family Support Center Project (Famispo), which connects parents who want to temporarily leave their children and support members who take care of them at private homes, have independently strengthened safety measures.
Prior to the provision of free child education and childcare in October, the family members of the childcare accident complained that the country should make strict standards.
The "network to eliminate serious accidents in childcare" created by parents and experts who lost their children in a child-care accident was investigated by 921 municipalities.
274 municipalities responded.
The state's guidelines only require aid members to take emergency lifesaving courses.
