[Saga Torrential Rainfall and Support Wheel] Specialty Noodles "Taromen" Perform at evacuation centers Management Co-op, Revitalizing Victims|Saga Shimbun News|Saga Shimbun
Children who enjoy "Taromen," the soul food of Omachi on their way home from the bath - Misato, Omachi Town General Welfare Center
"Omachi Taromen Steering Council" (Representative of Kensuke Suzuyama) made at a restaurant serving "Taromen," a specialty noodle of Omachi Town, performed "Taromen" at Misato, Machi General Welfare Center, which is a shelter for the victims of heavy rain on the night of the 25th.
It was a soul food loved since the Kishima coal mine was there, and cheered the people affected.
"What we can do is to make and eat taromen."
Four restaurants on the taromen menu cooperated to make 90 meals and brought rice balls to shelter.
Udon noodles with thin noodles were added to the beef bone soup with ginger, and ingredients such as pork head meat, shrimp, and vegetables were abundant.
Not only those who stayed in evacuation centers, but also those who came to the baths provided "taste of Omachi."
A man (66) says, "I've been a fan since I was young, but I've eaten it for the first time in a year," and a 20-year-old and 22-year-old siblings who moved about a year ago and said, "I ate it for the first time, it's delicious, I want to go to the store this time."
Vice Representative Kenichiro Fujise, who finished cooking, also ran up and said, "We will cooperate if we can, so that we can return quickly and always."
1 year from the earthquake in eastern Iburi Province Water supply even in the event of a power outage Establishment of a water sprinkling plug directly connected to a water pipe Hakodate Mansion: Hokkaido Shimbun
In response to the total blackout (blackout) caused by the Iburi Eastern Earthquake in September last year, measures are being taken at condominiums in Hakodate City, where water breaks out.
According to the Water and Sewer Department of the City Bureau of Enterprises, seven condominiums in one year after the earthquake installed "watering plugs" that could produce water even if power outages occurred.
There are about 400 condominiums and private housing units in the city that are more than four-story buildings that are watered by a "passenger tank" that can be dewatered during a power outage.
The house's water supply system is broadly divided into two types: the "passenger tank type" that once feeds water into a receiving tank located underground or on the roof, and the "direct connection type" that directly feeds water from the city's water distribution pipe to each door.
Even if the water pipe is not damaged, electric pumps that pump water from the water tank into each door will not be able to run due to power failure, and each door will be cut off.
Training (Aomori Broadcasting) - Yahoo!
A training session was held in Shingo Village to search for and rescue the victims before the autumn mushroom harvest season.
60 people from the police, fire and hunting party participated in the training held at Heikozawa Forest Park in Shingo Village.
At the opening ceremony, Chief Tsukeda of the Goto Police Department called for close cooperation and training.
★ Mr. Takahashi's declaration "We will start mountain training rescue training more than this."
The training was based on the assumption that a man who went out to see the mushroom harvest would not return home even at night.
Participants are divided into three groups and search through the mountains with the names of missing men.
In Shingo Village, a 70-year-old man who entered the mountain in June to pick wild vegetables disappeared and was rescued the next day.
During the training, I found a man who had been injured and checked the cooperation between searching and rescue on a stretcher to go down the mountain.
