Image of a new children's play facility in Kataya, Yamagata City
The children's play facility is scheduled to be built on the north side of Yamagata Kuchu in Katayachi District, with an area of approximately 23400 square meters.
The building has a total floor area of about 3,000 square meters.
It has a semi-underground gymnasium, cafe and book corner.
It also features universal design playground equipment for children with disabilities to play outdoors, ensuring 300 parking spaces.
On the 5th of this month, a committee meeting was held at the city hall, and 13 shelter groups (Yamagata City) won the bid for 30.5 million yen including design, preparation for opening, maintenance and operation expenses for 15 years.
It will enter design and construction in January next year, and will open in March 2022.
Image of Minaminumabara Elementary School
The school has over 900 pupils.
It is planned to be built on the north side of the current school building in Iizawa, and the site area is about 25,000 square meters.
It is a three-story reinforced concrete building with a total floor area of approximately 8580 square meters.
There are 30 classrooms, two pools, a steel gymnasium, and a post-school children's club.
At the review committee meeting on June 6, the Ichimura Corporation Group (Yamagata City), consisting of eight companies, won the bid for 4.512.1 million yen including design, demolition costs for the old school building, and maintenance and operation costs for 15 years.
It was designed and built in December and is expected to be completed in October 2010.
