Publication of his manuscript before Akutagawa suicide | Shizuoka Shimbun at Es
A manuscript written by Ryunosuke Akutagawa, first published in the Tabata Bunshimura Memorial Hall
The author Ryunosuke AKUTAGAWA (1892-1927) obtained the manuscript of his essay "Shoku Bunshi-mura Memorial Hall" in Kita Ward, Tokyo by 27 days, which he published in his last years, in which he fought literary theory with Junichiro TANIZAKI.
It will be exhibited at the museum from October 1.
Although it was known that his essay was included in the whole collection, it was the first time that his manuscript was published publicly.
It is thought that he wrote it a few months before Akutagawa committed suicide, and the memorial researcher, Takeshi Tanei, said, "I can see how Akutagawa, who had been debilitating both physically and mentally, faced serious literary challenges with a tragic resolution."
A total of 12 essays were published in the April 27 issue of Bungei Shunju.
