Jaguar F-PACE, the first major improvement ...The possibility of hybridization (response) - Yahoo!
Jaguar's first crossover SUV, "F-PACE" The camera captured the new prototype for the first time in Southern Europe.
F-PACE originated from the 4-seater concept SUV C-X17, which was first released in 2013.
The five-seater version was released in 2014 and officially debuted at the Frankfurt Motor Show in 2015.
In 2016, the first model was released, and this is the first facelift.
The prototype captured is covered with thick camouflage, but part of the new design can be seen.
The headlights are more compact and thin, and the side air intake is also modified to a sporty oval.
The grill is completely disguised, but there is no doubt that it will be redesigned.
In the rear end, a portion of the redesigned taillight can be seen with a long, narrow reverse light at the top.
As in the current model, there is a possibility that the design that revolves around the side is compactly modified.
In the cabin, the company's touch screen infotainment system is expected to be installed, and new digital clusters, HVAC control screens, steering wheels, and gear selectors will be refreshed.
The powertrain is expected to include a 2.0-liter inline four-cylinder turbodiesel as well as a hybrid 3.0-liter inline six-cylinder indium.
The world premiere will be in 2020.
