Okayama Art Exchange Opens in the City Center: Sanyo Shimbun Digital | Sanyo Digital
People around the classroom who will be the setting for a video work depicting the future 3,000 years later
The international art exhibition "Okayama Art Exchange 2019" held every three years in central Okayama City (hosted by the executive committee of cities and prefectures) opened on the 27th.
Along with the enigmatic title "IF THE SNAKE If Snake," 18 artists from 9 countries enjoy cutting-edge art.
This time, the second time since 16 years, we have invited French artist Pierre Yuig as artistic director, and have developed works that utilize Okayama's climate and local resources.
About 40 films and three-dimensional works will be shown at 13 locations including former Uchiyama Shimoko (Marunouchi, Kita Ward, Okayama City) and the prefectural Tenjinyama Cultural Plaza (Marunouchi, Kita Ward, Okayama City).
Prior to the opening ceremony, a small opening ceremony was held, and about 100 people attended.
Mayor Masao Omori and general producer Yasuharu Ishikawa, the chairman of the executive committee, said, "The works that stimulate intellectual sensibilities and stimulate imagination and creativity are scattered, and it becomes an exhibition that attracts attention from the world."
Families and children studying outside the school visited the school immediately and found a snake-shaped robot that responds to the surrounding sounds in the dohyo of the school yard, and walked around the school building, which turned into a stage for video works depicting the world 3,000 years later.
I enjoyed the art that led to different worlds.
While traveling with his father, a first-year student in Tokyo (15) said, "It's interesting to have a work that takes advantage of the atmosphere of the old school building, and I can imagine the time that flows into this place."
It is closed on November 24 (the following day if it is a national holiday).
Hong Kong rally in 5 years of rain umbrella movement tens of thousands, aiming for general election | Shizuoka Shimbun at Es
Five years have passed since the "Umbrella Movement" began, and people gathered at the meeting venue = 28th, Hong Kong (Joint)
[Collaboration with Hong Kong] On the 28th of May 2014, a large-scale demonstration called the "Umbrella Movement," which sought democratization of the election of the Hong Kong Secretary of State, was held in a park near the Hong Kong government headquarters building of the Admiralty, which had its largest base.
Some young people occupied the main road around the venue and threw fire bottles into the government building.
As protests started with the amendment of the Fugitive Ordinance continued, the participants renewed their determination to fight until the realization of a "true ordinary election" that could not be won at the time.
In June, more than 79 days after the Umbrella Movement, 112 days after the full-scale protests began, and the demands of the demonstrators expanded to "five major demands" such as electoral reform.
Ibaraki Kokutai Opening Day|Saga Shimbun News|Saga Shimbun
The 74th National Sports Festival "Ikiiki Ibaraki Yume National Sports Festival 2019" was held on October 28 at Kasamatsu Sports Park Athletic Stadium in Hitachinaka City, Ibaraki Prefecture.
About 400 athletes and directors from Saga Prefecture competed in 33 sports, excluding the pre-session of the festival.
The prefecture ranked 43rd for three consecutive years until last year, but rose to 33rd last year.
This year, we aim to reach the first half of the 20th place.
In the pre-season games held by the 16th, the Saga Girls' High School of rhythmic gymnastics boys and girls, and the adult girls and boys' girls of gymnastics all finished sixth.
I want to advance to the top in each competition by riding the flow.
At the general opening ceremony, 83 athletes, directors, and officers of the headquarters of the prefecture marched on the 40th entrance, and a rugby boy, Kugo Ishikawa (Saga Koka), was the flag bearer.
On the first day, wrestling, table tennis and karate are held.
